[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":526},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F12\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F12\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F12\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F12\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions\u002F":501,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F12\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions\u002F":510},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20191012\u002F2524618181\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":484,"date":485,"description":486,"extension":487,"lang":488,"meta":489,"navigation":262,"path":490,"readingMinutes":491,"seo":492,"standalone":493,"stem":494,"tags":495,"tldr":498,"updated":485,"url":499,"__hash__":500},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fjs-from-zero-ep27-es6-arrow-functions.md","ES6 Arrow Functions: Less Typing, But Watch Out for `this`","1002177728",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":479},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,36,39,96,105,142,145,175,183,215,225,236,341,344,425,452,461,465,475],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Day 27 of being reincarnated into JS. This post is all about ES6 arrow functions.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"arrow-functions","Arrow functions",[17,25,26,27,31,32,35],{},"As a developer, typing less is honestly always a win. ES6 gave us a new way to define functions to speed things up — you just swap the original ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"function"," keyword for ",[28,33,34],{},"=>",". That's what an arrow function is.",[17,37,38],{},"Here's a traditional anonymous function:",[40,41,46],"pre",{"className":42,"code":43,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","let myname = function () {\n  console.log('Ray');\n}\n","js","",[28,47,48,71,90],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,50,53,57,61,64,67],"span",{"class":51,"line":52},"line",1,[49,54,56],{"class":55},"sWyjQ","let",[49,58,60],{"class":59},"sj_SG"," myname",[49,62,63],{"class":55}," =",[49,65,66],{"class":55}," function",[49,68,70],{"class":69},"sMAXC"," () {\n",[49,72,74,77,80,83,87],{"class":51,"line":73},2,[49,75,76],{"class":69},"  console.",[49,78,79],{"class":59},"log",[49,81,82],{"class":69},"(",[49,84,86],{"class":85},"sTRMh","'Ray'",[49,88,89],{"class":69},");\n",[49,91,93],{"class":51,"line":92},3,[49,94,95],{"class":69},"}\n",[17,97,98,99,101,102,104],{},"Every time you want to create a function, you have to type out eight characters — ",[28,100,30],{},". But with ES6 you only type two: ",[28,103,34],{},". So that anonymous function above becomes this:",[40,106,108],{"className":42,"code":107,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"let myname = () => {\n  console.log('Ray');\n}\n",[28,109,110,126,138],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,111,112,114,116,118,121,123],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,113,56],{"class":55},[49,115,60],{"class":59},[49,117,63],{"class":55},[49,119,120],{"class":69}," () ",[49,122,34],{"class":55},[49,124,125],{"class":69}," {\n",[49,127,128,130,132,134,136],{"class":51,"line":73},[49,129,76],{"class":69},[49,131,79],{"class":59},[49,133,82],{"class":69},[49,135,86],{"class":85},[49,137,89],{"class":69},[49,139,140],{"class":51,"line":92},[49,141,95],{"class":69},[17,143,144],{},"Right away the code feels a lot cleaner. But here's the thing — the original named function definition looks like this:",[40,146,148],{"className":42,"code":147,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"function fu () {\n  console.log('Ray');\n}\n",[28,149,150,159,171],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,151,152,154,157],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,153,30],{"class":55},[49,155,156],{"class":59}," fu",[49,158,70],{"class":69},[49,160,161,163,165,167,169],{"class":51,"line":73},[49,162,76],{"class":69},[49,164,79],{"class":59},[49,166,82],{"class":69},[49,168,86],{"class":85},[49,170,89],{"class":69},[49,172,173],{"class":51,"line":92},[49,174,95],{"class":69},[17,176,177,178,182],{},"And you ",[179,180,181],"em",{},"can't"," just convert a regular named function into an arrow function like this:",[40,184,186],{"className":42,"code":185,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"fu () => {\n  console.log('Ray');\n}\n",[28,187,188,199,211],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,189,190,193,195,197],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,191,192],{"class":59},"fu",[49,194,120],{"class":69},[49,196,34],{"class":55},[49,198,125],{"class":69},[49,200,201,203,205,207,209],{"class":51,"line":73},[49,202,76],{"class":69},[49,204,79],{"class":59},[49,206,82],{"class":69},[49,208,86],{"class":85},[49,210,89],{"class":69},[49,212,213],{"class":51,"line":92},[49,214,95],{"class":69},[17,216,217,218,221,222,224],{},"There's also another catch with arrow functions — the ",[28,219,220],{},"this"," part. Inside an arrow function, ",[28,223,220],{}," behaves differently from a traditional function. Let me show you an example.",[17,226,227,228,230,231,235],{},"For a traditional function, ",[28,229,220],{}," is determined by ",[232,233,234],"strong",{},"how the function is called",":",[40,237,239],{"className":42,"code":238,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"var myname = '我是路人';\n\nvar a = {\n  myname: 'Ray',\n  fu: function () {\n    console.log(this.myname);\n  }\n}\na.fu(); \u002F\u002F Ray\n",[28,240,241,258,264,275,286,299,315,321,326],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,242,243,246,249,252,255],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,244,245],{"class":55},"var",[49,247,248],{"class":69}," myname ",[49,250,251],{"class":55},"=",[49,253,254],{"class":85}," '我是路人'",[49,256,257],{"class":69},";\n",[49,259,260],{"class":51,"line":73},[49,261,263],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":262},true,"\n",[49,265,266,268,271,273],{"class":51,"line":92},[49,267,245],{"class":55},[49,269,270],{"class":69}," a ",[49,272,251],{"class":55},[49,274,125],{"class":69},[49,276,278,281,283],{"class":51,"line":277},4,[49,279,280],{"class":69},"  myname: ",[49,282,86],{"class":85},[49,284,285],{"class":69},",\n",[49,287,289,292,295,297],{"class":51,"line":288},5,[49,290,291],{"class":59},"  fu",[49,293,294],{"class":69},": ",[49,296,30],{"class":55},[49,298,70],{"class":69},[49,300,302,305,307,309,312],{"class":51,"line":301},6,[49,303,304],{"class":69},"    console.",[49,306,79],{"class":59},[49,308,82],{"class":69},[49,310,220],{"class":311},"sCcAr",[49,313,314],{"class":69},".myname);\n",[49,316,318],{"class":51,"line":317},7,[49,319,320],{"class":69},"  }\n",[49,322,324],{"class":51,"line":323},8,[49,325,95],{"class":69},[49,327,329,332,334,337],{"class":51,"line":328},9,[49,330,331],{"class":69},"a.",[49,333,192],{"class":59},[49,335,336],{"class":69},"(); ",[49,338,340],{"class":339},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F Ray\n",[17,342,343],{},"But what if you switch it to an arrow function?",[40,345,347],{"className":42,"code":346,"language":44,"meta":45,"style":45},"var myname = '我是路人';\n\nvar a = {\n  myname: 'Ray',\n  fu: () => {\n    console.log(this.myname);\n  }\n}\na.fu(); \u002F\u002F 我是路人\n",[28,348,349,361,365,375,383,394,406,410,414],{"__ignoreMap":45},[49,350,351,353,355,357,359],{"class":51,"line":52},[49,352,245],{"class":55},[49,354,248],{"class":69},[49,356,251],{"class":55},[49,358,254],{"class":85},[49,360,257],{"class":69},[49,362,363],{"class":51,"line":73},[49,364,263],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":262},[49,366,367,369,371,373],{"class":51,"line":92},[49,368,245],{"class":55},[49,370,270],{"class":69},[49,372,251],{"class":55},[49,374,125],{"class":69},[49,376,377,379,381],{"class":51,"line":277},[49,378,280],{"class":69},[49,380,86],{"class":85},[49,382,285],{"class":69},[49,384,385,387,390,392],{"class":51,"line":288},[49,386,291],{"class":59},[49,388,389],{"class":69},": () ",[49,391,34],{"class":55},[49,393,125],{"class":69},[49,395,396,398,400,402,404],{"class":51,"line":301},[49,397,304],{"class":69},[49,399,79],{"class":59},[49,401,82],{"class":69},[49,403,220],{"class":311},[49,405,314],{"class":69},[49,407,408],{"class":51,"line":317},[49,409,320],{"class":69},[49,411,412],{"class":51,"line":323},[49,413,95],{"class":69},[49,415,416,418,420,422],{"class":51,"line":328},[49,417,331],{"class":69},[49,419,192],{"class":59},[49,421,336],{"class":69},[49,423,424],{"class":339},"\u002F\u002F 我是路人\n",[17,426,427,428,430,431,434,435,438,439,441,442,444,445,447,448,451],{},"Basically, wherever you define the thing, that's where ",[28,429,220],{}," points. In the arrow function example above, we defined ",[28,432,433],{},"var a = {};"," on ",[28,436,437],{},"window",", so ",[28,440,220],{}," points to ",[28,443,437],{},". In short, the ",[28,446,220],{}," inside an arrow function is ",[232,449,450],{},"bound to wherever it was defined",".",[17,453,454,455,457,458,460],{},"So in general, if I'm using ",[28,456,220],{},", I personally switch back to a traditional function — that way I can make sure ",[28,459,220],{}," points where I actually want it to.",[12,462,464],{"id":463},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,466,467,468,471,472,451],{},"The next post in RE: Starting Life in JS From Zero — Day 27 will cover the ES6 ",[28,469,470],{},"forEach"," and ",[28,473,474],{},"for...of",[476,477,478],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html